---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <main data-nt-section="home">
    <!-- HERO -->
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-pad-top">
        <h1>You Built a Business. Learning Digital Systems Shouldn't Be the Cost of Running It.</h1>

        <p>
          Too many owners get pulled into managing dashboards, chasing metrics, and decoding vendor jargon - just to make sure their online presence isn't quietly working against them.
          <br /><br />
          We take that weight off — and replace it with proof.
        </p>

        <div class="cta-row">
          <a
            class="btn btn-primary"
            href="/dcs-diagnostic/"
            data-nt-event="cta_primary"
            data-nt-cta="run_digital_credibility_score"
          >
            Run Your Digital Credibility Score
          </a>

          <a
            class="btn btn-secondary"
            href="#promptcore"
            data-nt-event="cta_secondary"
            data-nt-cta="learn_the_system"
          >
            See How the System Works
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SECTION 2: Problem Reframe -->
    <section data-nt-section="problem_reframe" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>The Problem You’re Actually Facing</h2>
        <p>
          If you've ever questioned whether your website, analytics, or marketing are actually telling you the truth—you're not alone.
          Most owners aren’t struggling because they’re doing something wrong. They’re struggling because their digital presence was never built to give clear, trustworthy answers in the first place.
        </p>
        <p>
          Effort isn’t the issue. Intelligence isn’t the issue. The issue is that most digital setups were never designed as systems.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 3: Why Digital Feels Hard -->
    <section data-nt-section="why_digital_hard" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Why Digital Feels Harder Than It Should</h2>
        <p>In most businesses, the digital side grows in pieces:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>A website that looks fine but doesn’t clearly earn trust</li>
          <li>Numbers that move but don’t explain what’s actually happening</li>
          <li>Vendors who optimize their part, not the whole</li>
          <li>Reports that require interpretation instead of delivering clarity</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The result is activity without confidence. You’re managing inputs without knowing which ones matter.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 4: What's Missing -->
    <section data-nt-section="whats_missing" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>What’s Missing Isn’t Another Tool</h2>
        <p>
          What’s missing isn’t more software, more campaigns, or another dashboard. What’s missing is a system that ties everything together—one that measures reality,
          builds credibility, and makes it obvious where to focus next.
        </p>

        <h3>A real digital system does three things consistently:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>It measures what actually matters</li>
          <li>It earns trust with platforms and customers</li>
          <li>It creates accountability across every digital decision</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          Most businesses never get this because no one owns the system end to end.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 5: Nextara Approach -->
    <section data-nt-section="nextara_approach" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>How Nextara Approaches the Problem</h2>
        <p>Nextara exists to design and govern that missing system.</p>
        <p>
          We don’t manage tactics in isolation or chase short-term wins. We build the structure behind your digital presence so you can see what’s working, what isn’t,
          and why—without having to decode it yourself.
        </p>
        <p>
          This turns your digital presence from a source of uncertainty into a source of clarity.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 6: Why This Works -->
    <section data-nt-section="why_this_works" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Why This Approach Works</h2>
        <p>
          When your digital presence is governed as a system, decisions stop being reactive. Assumptions get replaced with evidence. Confidence comes from proof, not reassurance.
        </p>
        <p>
          Growth becomes something you can trust—because it’s built on what can be verified, not what sounds good in a report.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROMPTCORE REVEAL -->
    <section id="promptcore" data-nt-section="promptcore_reveal" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>How We Replace Uncertainty With Proof</h2>

        <p>
          For most business owners, the hardest part of digital isn’t effort—it’s uncertainty. You’re making decisions without knowing which signals to trust,
          which numbers matter, or whether your online presence is helping or quietly holding you back.
        </p>

        <p>This is the gap PromptCore was built to close.</p>

        <h3>The Digital Credibility Score</h3>

        <p>
          PromptCore produces a <strong>Digital Credibility Score</strong>—a clear, defensible measure of how trustworthy your digital presence appears to both humans and machines.
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Human Trust (PromptCore v3.6)</strong><br />
            Evaluates what real people experience: clarity, credibility signals, accessibility, consistency, and whether your digital presence feels legitimate and trustworthy.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Machine Trust (PromptCore v3.7)</strong><br />
            Evaluates what platforms see: technical integrity, structured data, performance, security, analytics hygiene, and whether your site can be confidently interpreted and indexed.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          Together, these lenses answer the question most businesses can’t get a straight answer to today:
          <em>Can my digital presence be trusted—and proven—by the systems that decide visibility, ranking, and conversion?</em>
        </p>

        <p>
          When credibility is unclear, growth is fragile. Decisions are based on assumptions, reports require interpretation, and confidence depends on reassurance.
          When credibility is measured, growth becomes stable. You can see what’s real, identify what’s missing, and fix problems before they compound.
        </p>

        <p>This is how we take the weight off—and replace it with proof.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 7: Fit & Focus -->
    <section data-nt-section="fit_focus" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Fit & Focus</h2>
        <p><strong>Designed for operators who want to know the truth about what’s working—and act on it.</strong></p>
        <p>
          Nextara is built for owners who care about doing things right and want their digital presence to reflect the quality of how they run their business.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you’re looking for quick tactics, shortcuts, or surface-level optimization, this won’t be a fit.
          If you want clarity, accountability, and a system you can rely on, you’re in the right place.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA BLOCK (AFTER FIT & FOCUS) -->
    <section data-nt-section="cta_block" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Ready to See Where You Stand?</h2>
        <p>
          Run your Digital Credibility Score to see what’s helping, what’s missing, and what to fix first.
        </p>

        <div class="cta-row">
          <a
            class="btn btn-primary"
            href="/dcs-diagnostic/"
            data-nt-event="cta_primary"
            data-nt-cta="run_digital_credibility_score"
          >
            Run Your Digital Credibility Score
          </a>

          <a
            class="btn btn-secondary"
            href="#promptcore"
            data-nt-event="cta_secondary"
            data-nt-cta="learn_the_system"
          >
            See How the System Works
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
